Richard of York, Duke of York
1411-1460
Quarterly, 1st and 4th, France modern, 2nd and 3rd England, with a label of three points Argent each point charged with three torteaux Gules[18]
Son of: Richard of Conisburgh, Earl of Cambridge, Duke of York and Anne Mortimer.
Originator of the claim of the House of York to the throne.
Defeated and killed at the Battle of Wakefield in 1460.








Cecily Neville, Duchess of York
1415-1495
Gules a saltire Argent (Neville)[18]
Daughter of: Ralph de Neville, Earl of Westmorland and Joan Beaufort(daughter of John of Gaunt).
Married to: Richard of York, Duke of York; 1429-1460.





