Company Overview of American Chemistry Council, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Edward Arthur Rose IIIDirector, American Chemistry Council, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships----
Background

		Mr. Edward Arthur Rose, III, also known as Ed, served as an Executive Vice President and President of Performance Chemicals at Ingevity Corporation since May 15, 2016 until January 2017. Mr. Rose served as the President of MWV Specialty Chemicals Division at MeadWestvaco Corporation from November 10, 2009 to October 28, 2015. Mr. Rose joined MeadWestvaco Corporation in 1984 in Charleston in its Construction Chemicals Group, where he was responsible for the development ... of roadwork products and technologies. He began his career with Westvaco in 1984 in the Construction Chemicals Group where he was responsible for the development of road construction products and technologies that enabled rapid business expansion. He worked in sales at the Specialty Chemicals Division and also served as a Business Development Manager. He served as a Marketing Manager at the Polychemicals Department, where he led a team developing new products for the textile, agricultural and pine chemicals markets. Since 2003, he served as Vice President of Meadwestvaco's Performance Chemicals business in the Specialty Chemical Division. Mr. Rose serves as a Director at American Chemistry Council, Inc. He holds a Bachelor of Science in Civil Engineering from Clemson University.Read Full Background




